{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Cloud*. Using *JIRA Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-64634].
  {panel}

We are going to start importing our old excel sheets containing issues into JIRA, and therefore I've tried out the csv importer. In our use case, I want to import issues only. Users, issue types etc are already set up in JIRA.

To my surprise, new issue types, users and other items are created automatically without any warning upon import. As we already have a fully configured JIRA environment with everything setup, I don't want the importer to create anything new. If it needs to, it is because I've made a mistake in the csv file or the mapping.

The importer should be able to issue a warning before adding new users, issue types or anything else belonging to the JIRA configuration.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Cloud*
  {panel}

Currently, to browse the options for a drop-down custom field, you need to use the scroll down/up function. It would be helpful if you could type the options, like in the system's native fields.

{panel:title=Status Update|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#ff7f7f|titleBGColor=#ff7f7f|bgColor=#e5e5e5}
A slightly outdated version of the code is available in the public atlaskit repo:
 - [https://bitbucket.org/atlassian/atlaskit-mk-2/src/master/packages/editor/editor-markdown-transformer/]

You can give it a try since for now it is not granted that an official endpoint will be released.

Example:
{noformat}
import { defaultSchema } from '@atlaskit/adf-schema';
import { JSONTransformer } from '@atlaskit/editor-json-transformer';
import { MarkdownTransformer } from '@atlaskit/editor-markdown-transformer';

const jsonTransformer = new JSONTransformer();
const markdownTransformer = new MarkdownTransformer(defaultSchema);

const markdownDocument = '';
const adfDocument = jsonTransformer.encode(markdownTransformer.parse(markdownDocument));
{noformat}
{panel}

h3. Summary

As written in the below thread in the Atlassian Community, up until some time ago there used to be the api [https://api.atlassian.com/pf-editor-service/convert?from=xxxx&to=xxx |https://api.atlassian.com/pf-editor-service/convert?from=markdown&to=adf%C2%A0]for converting Markdown, Markup, HTMl, etc  to Atlassian Document Format and vice-versa:
 - [Is there documentation for api.atlassian.com/pf-editor-service/convert?|https://community.atlassian.com/t5/Jira-questions/Is-there-documentation-for-api-atlassian-com-pf-editor-service/qaq-p/1743002]

 

By using this endpoint you could easily convert formats as described in below table:

!https://community.atlassian.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/150706i4285739522870843/image-dimensions/2000?v=v2&px=-1|width=413,height=245!

 

This endpoint was not documented and therefore not supported stopped and it was decommissioned around the beginning of September. It would be nice to get an official endpoint customers can use to easily convert among formats.
h3. Workaround

If you need to convert from ADF to HTML you can use the following workaround:
 * To get the comment body returned as HTML call [the GET /rest/api/3/[ISSUE KEY or ID]/comments|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/#api-rest-api-3-issue-issueIdOrKey-comment-get] endpoint and append *?**expand=renderedBody* to it:
{noformat}
https://NAME.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/issue/{ISSUE-KEY_OR_ID}/comment?expand=renderedBody
{noformat}

 * To get the issue description returned as HTML use the  [/rest/api/3/issue/\{issueIdOrKey}|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/api-group-issues/#api-rest-api-3-issue-issueidorkey-get]  endpoint followed by *?**expand=renderedFields*:
{noformat}
https://NAME.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/issue/{ISSUE-KEY_OR_ID}?expand=renderedFields
{noformat}
